node.title: EU Leaders Set to Vote on Regulation of Big Tech, Including Targeted Ads, Porn Sites
node.description: Lawmakers in the 27-nation bloc have proposed rules that would make tech companies more responsible for content uploaded to their sites and keep them from stopping competitors.

node.title: Trump Tells AP Not to Make 'Fool Out of Yourself' Over Its Investigation Into Voter Fraud
node.description: The AP conducted a review of over 400 voter fraud cases in the 2020 election across six battleground states, and found that none made an impact on the election.

node.title: Pro-Trump Attorney Lin Wood Cleared in Georgia Election Investigation
node.description: The investigation was launched once it was heard from a television reporter that Wood possibly had been living in South Carolina when he voted.

node.title: Arizona Asks SCOTUS to Allow Abortion Ban on Cases Involving Genetic Abnormalities
node.description: Mark Brnovich, Arizona's Republican attorney general, is hoping for the ban to finally be implemented after numerous setbacks.
